  "text": "EHS Training\nTraining Plan\nEHS training program is designed to enhance awareness, build competencies, and ensure compliance among all stakeholders involved in laboratory and operational safety. The program focuses on developing a shared responsibility matrix, delivering targeted training courses, and fostering a proactive safety culture.\nEHS has established the training matrix as below.\nTraining Courses\nLab Safety Rules\nGeneral Awareness of Lab Safety Rules\nEmergency Shower and Eye Wash\nHow to Use Emergency Shower and Eye Wash\nPersonal Protection Equipment\nDress Code and PPE Requirement in Labs\nWastes Disposal in Lab\nProper Disposal of Various Wastes in Lab\nSoliding\nSafe Usage, Electrical Safety, Fire Safety and First Aid of Soldering\nEthylene Oxide Concerns\nSafety Usage of Ethylene Oxide Concerns\nCampus Safety\nService Line (24/7): + 86 21 2059 5500 Email: shanghai.safety@nyu.edu Address: E118, 1F East Hall, the New Bund Campus, 567 Yangsi W Rd.",
